The free variable is counter

what is free variable?
free variable is a variable which is neither declared inside a function(inner) nor passed 
as an parameter (arguement) to the function.
a clusure is defined when a function (inner) that has free variables is defined, the free variables 
are variables from the surrounding environment.

a closure instance is created when an inner function assigned to a variable and attached to it self to 
free variables.